name: Velox Coffee
directions: In the back of the store

name: Starbucks
directions: On the east wall, to the right of the counter, and through a door labeled as restrooms. Two restrooms available.
comment: Preferred paying customer, but the outside door is very close to the bathrooms for a swift exit if you just need to make a bathroom stop.

name: Acute Salon
directions: Look for the large triangle mural on the side of the building
comment: This is a gender neutral trans - friendly salon!

name: Cedar Ridge High School Performing Arts Center
directions: Not in the main school building, in the Performing Arts Center in front. If you come through the front doors, go on the right side past the staircase, and there’s a small hallway to the right. There’s a women’s restroom and a gender-neutral family restroom.

name: NYIT-Whitney Lane House
directions: Located on the First Floor

name: NYIT-Green Lodge
directions: On the Second Floor

name: NYIT-deSeversky Mansion
directions: On the First Floor Near Stairwell Leading to NYCOMEC Area. For Driving Directions when on campus, follow the posted signs to the Mansion.

name: NYIT-Harry J. Schure Hall, Whitney Ln, Glen Head, NY 11545, USA
directions: On the First Floor

name: 751 US-202 BUS, New Britain, PA 18901, USA
directions: in the hallway, near the women’s restroom

name: The Good Measure
comment: The Good Measure is a pretty cool little pub which seems dedicated to making it welcome to all.

name: Espace Vie Étudiante - E.V.E., 72000 Le Mans, France
Kylie Ferry
comment: You don’t have to buy anything at all I work here and it’s totally a safe place for all. I’m a married lesbian!

name: Publix Supermarket at Willow Oaks Crossing
directions: Front of store.

name: Starbucks
comment: Both single bathrooms are gendered neutral. Walk in, go straight ahead. No lock code needed.

name: Olde Nola Cookery
comment: Paying customers only

name: Progressive Living
directions: come in and ask receptionist to use restroom, they will direct you
comment: small office building on corner of 2nd and madison, 9-5 weekdays. fulltime receptionist is nonbinary and will let you use it no questions asked. free cold water available as well

name: Walmart
directions: Back of store in orange pickup

name: Memorial Union
directions: Right next to the Cardinal Room, near hotel lobby
comment: Bathroom is accessible but the door is heavy

name: Brown University Library
directions: Third Floor
comment: Unfortunately, you need to either have a brown ID or one of the other visitor arrangements listed here: https://library.brown.edu/libweb/visitors.php

name: Cecil Sharp House
directions: Ask at reception and they'll show you the way
comment: Friendly staff, not too busy. Always clean and spacious.

name: London Grill
directions: Across from the bar on first floor.

name: Sackville Sports Stadium
directions: Inclusive washroom is located on the pool level of the facility. Enter the facility at the aquatics entrance (2nd set of doors if you come in from the main road) and go down the stairs past the front desk.
comment: Because the inclusion washroom is located on the pool level you will have to alert the front desk person where you are going. If you don’t feel comfortable telling the staff you need to use the inclusion washroom, you can always tell them you are checking the lost and found because it is located on the pool level. Staff at the SSS is trained in inclusion and understand people have different needs.

name: West High School
directions: On the second floor. Enter through the front doors, go right at the panther statue and enter the first hallway you see. You should pass by a female bathroom. The gender neutral bathroom is next to the elevator. There is a female faculty restroom right next to it, but it is locked.
comment: Restrooms are for students and visitors. As long as you act causal and look young, you shouldn't be bothered by administration.

name: Gala ice cream shop
directions: All there bathrooms are unisex

name: Cast Cafe
directions: Ground floor
comment: Accessible when the building is open and not attached to the cafe. If you are in the cafe it is directly out of the door and down the ground floor corridor.

name: Boston Burger Company
directions: Straight back to the hallway past the bar, on the right
comment: the bathroom even has a funny sign about not caring about gender! :)

name: Martha Kensington
directions: Both gender neutral single stall restrooms are just inside the entrance to the right. The one on the left has a changing table.
comment: Not sure if you need to be a paying customer.

name: LimeRed Teahouse
comment: Steep stairs and heavy door in the entrance

name: McKay Used Books
directions: Down aisle 9 to the end, then take a right.
comment: Changing table is in left single stall room.

name: Centre For Social Innovation - Spadina Avenue
directions: Walk down the laneway on the south side of the building to the entrance to the Toronto Tool Library on the south side near the back of the building. Walk down a small flight of stairs and the single-stall washrooms will be right in front of you.

name: Spectrum
directions: All their bathrooms are designated as any gender. Single stalls with one accessible, one not in front and the same in back.

name: Hillman Center for Performing Arts
directions: lower level, next to the green room: near the theater’s emergency/handicap accessible exit/entrance
comment: if you’re on campus for an event at the Hillman, this is the one family bathroom in the building

name: Walmart neighborhood
directions: To the left nearby the pharmacy its the single restroom
comment: Sometimes theres a few minute wait, you can wait by the pharmacy bench.

name: Starbucks
comment: you do not have to be a paying customer, but you have to ask for the bathroom code

name: Marathon Gas
directions: Single stall restroom inside the store
comment: Restrooms are for paying customers, but I doubt they strictly enforce it. This is the country though, the kind of place to be careful! Cops are usually not in town and take a long time (25+ minutes) to arrive from Potterville. Cell service is spotty. Amish buggies everywhere

name: Quicken Loans
directions: Restrooms are in the basement. Take the elevator down 1 flight.
comment: There is a rotating art exhibition space on the first floor that is open to the public. You must be a visiting an exhibit or a Quicken Loans employee to use the restroom. Restrooms have many stalls. The doors say Self-idenified man and Self-idenified woman.

name: Yukon High School
directions: In the theatre room (labeled

name: 10 W Main St, Yukon, OK 73099, USA
directions: In the back

name: Little Caesar's Pizza
directions: to the far right when you enter

name: USC Village Fitness Center
directions: By the locker rooms and other bathrooms
comment: You must have an active membership

name: I-75 NB Rest Area at MM 46.7
directions: On the women's side of the building, closer to the east side of the building.
comment: Usually available 24/7, but unable to verify accessibility as all restrooms were locked (due to nearby wildfires, I'm guessing).  Used in Feb 2019 all indications were that they are 24/7.  Very accessible.

name: Drury Inn & Suites
directions: Just inside the main entrance to the right of the registration counter.
comment: All doors remained locked from exterior must use main entrance.  I have used several times never been questioned.  You can exit the side door to avoid going through the lobby.

name: Earth Cup Cafe
comment: Just ask to use bathroom, you probably don’t have to buy anything, everyone working is really chill

name: Gunzo's Sports
directions: Back right, past counter
comment: Restroom is unisex but store is very cis-masculine environment; individual customers and/or staff may not be tolerant.

name: Native American Cultural Center
directions: Next to the other restrooms by the south entrance

name: Starbucks
directions: Two separate single stall bathrooms to the right after walking in

name: Amesbury Public Library
directions: In basement.
comment: Key needed for door of restrooms. Obtain key at front desk. Each restroom is unisex.

name: Shortwave coffee
directions: Bathrooms are in back room to the left

name: Mill Woods Town Center Co-op
directions: Just to the left of the customer service desk by the main doors of the Co-op, on the NW corner of the mall.
comment:
Single-toilet bathroom with push-button lock on the inside door handle. You don't need to be a paying customer to use but unpurchased items must be left outside. There are accessibility bars by the toilet but the door is awkwardly stiff to open.
Special note: People coming from nearby festivities on July 1 often render it unusable before suppertime that day.

name: T4 South Sac
directions: The restroom is in the back to the left of the service counter. Ask at the counter for the restroom key.
comment: You may need to have a few dollars on hand to purchase a drink or snack. The restroom needs a key you can get by asking at the front counter.

name: Seattle Area Feline Rescue
comment:
It's in the back but just ask whoever is at the front to use it.
Hours: Thursday-Monday 1PM to 7PM

name: UMich School of Dentistry
directions: One on each floor
comment: The School of Dentistry has public clinics serving hundreds of people each week day. You will not stand out as “obviously not a student or employee.”

name: Adler University
directions: 15th floor marked "all gender"
comment: You have to be an Adler student, faculty, or staff member, or you have to be signed in by a student, faculty, or staff member.

name: Mcmenamins Bagdad Pub
directions: Main pub facing Hawthorne

name: National Videogame Museum
directions: To the right just before the check-in desk.
comment: Gender neutral toilet block and separate accessible toilet with changing table. Friendly staff for queer folk.

name: Oak-Elm Residence Hall
directions: Ground (2nd) floor near hall desk, and Oak Hall lobby

name: Maple Residence Hall
comment: All residential floors have single-stall, unisex restrooms and showers

name: JC Penney
directions: 2nd floor

name: Municipal Building, 350 S 5th St, Minneapolis, MN 55415, USA
directions: Just inside the courthouse, ground floor (G), near the adult & juvenile detention areas. Look at a map to locate restrooms, they're a bit hidden down narrow hallways. Restrooms are labelled unisex  and are single stall.

name: J Sargeant Reynolds Community College
directions: Go into Georgiadis hall. The Bathroom is within the cafe, which is on the main floor.
comment: You do not need to be a customer. You can just walk in

name: Landsdowne mall family room
directions: Near food court

name: Home Depot
directions: All the way to the left of the building. There is a family single stall restroom

name: Wow Bar
directions: Downstairs to the right
comment: Ask if you aren't buying anything.

name: Webster’s Bookstore and Cafe
directions: Two accessible and neutral stalls down the ramp from the front door. The second bathroom also has a free trans clothing closet if folks want to try on/need clothing!
comment: You do not have to be a paying customer, and the bathrooms are easily accessible via the ramp. Sometimes there is a wait, but Webster’s is a very safe space.

name: Bar Jeder Sicht
directions: Three steps on the first floor, you enter through the front door, go straight for about five meters, the toilets are on the right from the bar.
comment:
The toilets are "gendered" with additional signs saying as much as "if you do not see yourself as either male or female you can use whichever restroom you feel more comfortable with".

Also this place is an LGBT+ safe space.

name: Taliesin Arts Centre
directions: Ground floor of Taliesin arts centre
comment: Open to the public until the building closes- varies depending on if events are on

name: 655 Cheshire Rd, Lanesborough, MA 01237, USA
directions: By front entrance
comment: There are handicap stalls in the gendered restrooms as well as a unisex handicap restroom

name: Best Buy
directions: Go through the door in the back right corner of the store. Keep to the right.
comment: The gender neutral bathroom is in the auto install bay. The staff is very trans friendly (trans & non-binary people work here) so don't be afraid to use the gendered bathrooms by the computer department.

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back of the store .
comment: Single seat restrooms with doors that lock .

name: Luke's Lobster
directions: Straight back
comment: Its a very small restaurant

name: Foxwoods Casino
directions: Between Great Cedar Casino and Fox Tower Casino
comment: Just walk in and go through any security checks and then possibly ask for a map or other directions. It's easier than how I explained it. There are probably more all gender restrooms than this one as well so look around and have fun!

name: Belle’s Diner
directions: Middle of the restaurant
comment: Paying customers only

name: Target
directions: To left of store entrance
comment: No purchase required

name: Fuel Charleston
directions: Go inside and it’s to the left around a corner with the big glassy tile windows
comment: You don’t have to pay to use

name: Costa Coffee
directions: Downstairs, far side of the room
comment: One, non gender specific stall

name: Blend.co
directions: Back of the shop.
comment: You must be a paying customer

name: Duluth YMCA
directions: Through the turnstile and straight to your left.  There are two of them.
comment: You have to have a membership to get in but I believe you can ask to use the restroom.

name: Hawks and Reed Performing Arts Center
The 413
comment: Owners are super friendly and place is a safe space for LGBT folk.

name: Comal
directions: Towards the back of the first section of the restaurant, just past the kitchen on the right hand side.
comment: It's expected for you to be eating at the restaurant, so just act like you're heading to the bar area in the back.

name: Epicurious Garden
directions: First floor, on the right, past the first restaurant if you're coming from the street.
